text: Colanguil or Colangüil is a mountain range or area in Argentina. It has a height of . It's located at Iglesia Department, San Juan Province, at the Central Andes. == First Ascent == Colanguil was first climbed by Pedro Rosell (Argentina) and Humberto Campodónico (Argentina) in 15/12/1994. == Elevation == Based on the elevation provided by the available Digital elevation models, SRTM (6100m), ASTER (6076m), SRTM filled with ASTER (6100m), ALOS (6076m), TanDEM-X(6133m), Colanguil is about 6122 meters above sea level. The height of the nearest key col is 4575 meters. so its prominence is 1547 meters. Colanguil is listed as mountain range or area, based on the Dominance system and its dominance is 25.27%. Its parent peak is Majadita and the Topographic isolation is 97.8 kilometers. This information was obtained during a research by Suzanne Imber in 2014. == References == == External links == * Elevation information about Colanguil * Weather Forecast at Colanguil Category:Six- thousanders of the Andes
